gomodel:SYNGO_4115  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig2A-B: Human anti-EEA1 (blue) and mouse anti-synaptophysin antibodies (yellow) display distinct immunoreactivity in the CA3 field of the hippocampus. Antibodies against early endosome marker protein EEA1 produce a characteristic vesicular staining pattern in CA3 cell bodies and dendrites and do not co-localize with synaptophysin antibodies, which label the presynaptic nerve terminals but rather are in close proximity of Synaptophysin puncta (inset).\n\nFig 2C: Majority of EEA1 puncta (blue) colocalise with PSD-95 (yellow) on cultured hippocampal neurons.\n\nFigure 1: Independent antibody validation was performed to verify the specificity of the human-anti-EEA1 used in the study. Confocal images showed the co-localization of human anti-EEA1 (blue) and mouse monoclonal (yellow) anti-EEA1 antibodies in cultured COS-7 cells.. Experimental description: Hippocampal neurons were prepared from P0 C57 mice" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2916-7616" ;
        dc:date           "2022-08-05" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4115" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

